Thank you for a great interview with Dr. Fauci.
I do have a question regarding Dr. Fauci's answer to whether or not you can be infected with the Coronavirus twice: he didn't seem to have factored in the fact that the virus mutates. Also, there are studies that found that there are 2 types of Coronavirus instead of just one, and an Icelandic patient was found simultaneously infected with both types. Here is the report from the Icelandic national broadcaster RUV: https://www.ruv.is/frett/two-types-of-covid-19-in-one-individual
Here's a video discussing one of the studies of different strains of the Sars-cov-2 virus: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yWkRtVq7jcw


I'd love to hear your opinions on this. I have also watched Dr. Fauci's interview with the Daily Show's Trevor Noah, and both times he had stated that he doesn't believe reinfection is common or that one patient could be infected multiple times. It is curious why we haven't heard about the multiple strains and the mutation capability of the virus in any of the US mainstream media or major healthcare professional outlets.


Thank you for your time, and for your brave service and sacrifices for all of us. New York Tough!
